Here's the XAML and ViewModel setup:

## XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="Auto,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

## ViewModel (using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm)

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IItemService _itemService;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> _items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? _selectedItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isRefreshing;

    public ItemsViewModel(IItemService itemService)
    {
        _itemService = itemService;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _itemService.GetItemsAsync();
        Items = new ObservableCollection<Item>(data);
        IsRefreshing = false; // Must set false to hide spinner
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"detail?id={SelectedItem.Id}");
        SelectedItem = null; // Reset so user can re-select same item
    }
}
```

## Key Binding Points

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` (bool) | Set `false` when done loading |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Triggers API reload |
| `CollectionView.SelectedItem` | `SelectedItem` (TwoWay) | Holds current selection |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires on selection change |
| `ItemsSource` | `Items` (ObservableCollection) | Use ObservableCollection, not List |

**Important details:**
- Set `IsRefreshing = false` after loading — otherwise the spinner stays visible.
- Reset `SelectedItem = null` after navigation so the same item can be tapped again.
- Use `x:DataType` on the `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- Always use `ObservableCollection<T>` so add/remove updates the UI automatically.
